<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 24 at 11:16PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Beaver
County through 1145 PM CDT...
At 1115 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles south of Knowles, or 17 miles east of Beaver, moving northeast
at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Gate and Knowles.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
